phrases: Man, this week's storyboard is good too.
How did I do in the rankings this week?
I will keep working hard and come in 1st next week, too.
CROW's been ranked 1st three weeks in a row.
Catching up to him will not be as easy as we made it sound.
Apparently, Niizuma's been devoting a lot of time into revising his storyboards lately.
He is been working on them for days on end.
Maybe he is trying to egg us on?
Well, knowing that CROW is ranked 1st does make me feel more motivated...
It is Niizuma's way of lighting a fire under us!
We have got to surpass him in the rankings and return the favor!
Here is CROW and NATURAL's manuscripts.
Nothing has changed this week, either.
It is a seven year old promise, after all.
Um, Niizuma, congrats on CROW coming in 1st.
Think you can do something about NATURAL, too?
I have not been slacking on the art.
There is nothing wrong with the art.
But it is dropped in the rankings ever since the anime ended,
I know you are doing the art for both, but...
It is because the story for NATURAL is not interesting.
I am not the story writer.
If you want it to be popular,
you and Akina have to make the story compelling.
The latest chapters are pretty dull.
The story's turned into an endless repetition of defeating bad guys, each one stronger than the last.
Yes, it is the same pattern over and over again.
You two sure do not pull any punches.
The story might improve if I am allowed to make changes.
But I can only change so many things.
Akina has her pride, after all.
Forming a relationship with her similar to what Ashirogi Mutou has will not be easy.
At least NATURAL's manga volumes are still selling well...
Do you think Niizuma does not like the way NATURAL is dragging on?
It is certainly past its peak.
I am finding it hard to breathe when it is just the two of us, Nakai.
It is like there is less oxygen in here than there should be.
It is not like I actually want to be your assistant.
That is no reason to let the quality of your art drop, Nakai.
It will not match unless I drop my quality down to the level of your art.
Why do you insist on talking to me like we are buddies?
Are not I top dog here?
I get the feeling you think pretty highly of yourself.
Believe me, I would rather not speak to you like we are friends.
Because things are going well between you and Aoki, obviously!
Are you telling me you have not given up on her?!
Oh, I just got an idea!
I think we can use it.
I did give up on her, but I cannot help but feel jealous!
Do you have any idea how I feel, having to work with you?!
What I would give to have a girlfriend...
Why do not you ask Mr. Yoshida for advice?
It is no secret that my relationship with Aoki started by following advice from Mr. Yoshida.
Not even you can help him, Mr. Yoshida.
If I can make this work...
Do you really want a girlfriend?
You would be required to follow a diet plan that I would create for you.
However, that would lessen a negative influence on Hiramaru,
namely the financial burden of supporting your overeating habits.
Is that all you care about, Mr. Yoshida?!
But it is true that no matter how much you eat, that feedI mean, food,
is not a major source of negativity for Hiramaru at this point in time.
More important is the risk that you would succumb to obesity-related diseases.
Your skills as an assistant are practically wasted on Hiramaru.
If you truly intend to follow my teachings,
then I will rise to the challenge of transforming you into a Super Manga Author.
We will turn you into a first rate manga author in mind, manners, agility, and looks.
You will be able to turn the head of any womanAoki included!
I know you can do it!
I will give it a shot!
Start by running 10 km, mornings and evenings!
This tough love is necessary to keep your negativity flowing.
And if I can corrupt Nakai at the same time, that will be two birds with one stone.
This makes CROW's fourth consecutive week at 1st!
It is popularity is the real thing.
It is because he is making things exciting by having all the characters participate in a final battle.
Road Racer GIRI's anime just started, and now the manga is ranked right below us.
Once Seigi no Mikata's drama adaptation starts, it should skyrocket to the top of the rankings!
CROW's top ranking gave them some motivation.
About earning the right to end a manga?
I was worried that Niizuma might be going for that,
but it looks like he only has Ashirogi's best interests in mind.
If that is why he is so set on being in first, he will never come out and say it.
It is business as usual, then.
Also, Ashirogi wants you to know that CROW's top ranking has motivated them.
They just wanted to thank you.
I will become a Super Manga Author!
Wait, rankings are out today since the holiday break starts tomorrow, right?
I left them on top of your desk.
First place for five weeks in a row!
The anime must have bumped it up.
I am Hattori Yuujirou, editor of the 1st and 3rd ranked manga!
Just make me a team leader already!
Refusing on the basis of my youth is old-fashioned!
He is so full of himself!
Hard to argue with the 1st and 3rd rankings, though.
I am off to Fukuda's house!
Miura, you do not have time to be rejoicing.
GIRI beat us in the rankings?
PCP placing 4th is not so bad,
but it cannot outrank a manga that has an anime, let alone catch up to Niizuma.
I will never stop living on the edge!
It feels like he is going so fast!
It is only episode 3 and it is already this exciting!
With this, the manga's rankings and volume sales are sure to go up!
You came in 3rd place this week!
We are finally in the top three!
Getting first place might not be just a dream, after all!
Well, there is quite a gap between you and CROW.
You have got your work cut out for you.
Since you are already editing both, you will not give a damn if GIRI passes CROW, will you?
I would be thrilled if GIRI got the top spot!
Ideally, newer manga should surpass long-running ones.
But it would be really hard to surpass CROW.
It is come in first place for the last five weeks.
Niizuma being so set on coming in 1st had me feeling anxious for a while.
Niizuma asked for the right to end a manga he hates if he ever became the no. 1 author in Jack.
Needless to say, I told him he could not do that.
But the Chief told him, We will talk about it if you still feel that way once you have become our magazine's main attraction.
So what was the manga Niizuma wanted to end?
I have not asked him, you know.
But this was decided when he was serialized seven years ago.
Maybe the manga he wanted to end is already over.
And at this point in time, it would probably be NATURAL.
He said the story's boring and follows the same pattern over and over.
Are you sure you should be telling us this?
I know Niizuma will not bring that deal up again.
His fixation on being 1st is just to motivate Ashirogi.
Besides, he is matured during his years of being serialized.
CROW's come in first place five weeks in a row!
The story's getting exciting with the introduction of an all-out war.
And then we have PCP, which will never get an anime.
Saikou, do not you think it is about time we started thinking about another manga?
An unorthodox battle story with a mainstream character...
I have drawn the all-important mainstream character a few times.
No, they are not good enough.
I do not want to compromise.
I spoke with someone at the reception desk.
I did not hear anything about that.
I came to meet with the Chief Editor.
You are the only one left, Falcon!
You never cease to amaze me, Falcon.
Our moves are in perfect harmony.
But such perfect driving is not my...
Yuujirou's here to pick up the manuscript.
Right in the middle of the anime, again.
Only a madman would think of a move like that!
Cannot you let us watch the anime in peace?
Some girl would not give you the time of day or something?
He is usually all smiles, even when he gets rejected.
Yuujirou, CROW and GIRI had good rankings this week.
With the way things are looking,
And why do you look depressed about that?
Yuujirou, you must be upset over Master Niizuma.
Upset does not even begin to describe it.
Master Niizuma brought up the right to end a manga he hates, did not he?
And do not spread any... strange rumors!
He is so easy to read.
I wonder which manga Master Niizuma wants the right to end.
Last week, Yuujirou said it would probably be NATURAL.
Are we having this meeting or what?
The anime's over and the manga's ranking has plummeted.
That is why I told you to be careful.
Sorry, but I am in a meeting right now.
I will call back later, then.
On second thought, if you have something to tell me, you can say it now.
Um, I am not part of the so-called Team Fukuda.
But it is to discuss the possibility of Niizuma ending NATURAL...
We do not even know if Niizuma's actually been given the right to do this.
But it is also true that Niizuma showed up at the editing department on Monday and spoke to the Chief Editor.
I heard this from Mr. Yoshida.
Since they spoke in a separate room,
even Mr. Yoshida, a team leader, does not know what they talked about.
In other words, only Niizuma's editor, Yuujirou, knows.
And you know how Yuujirou's been acting.
It does seem likely that he was granted the right to end a manga.
No, maybe it is Never Reaching You!
Hiramaru, that is not something you should be happy about!
I still find it hard to believe that they would give him that right just because he came in 1st a few times.
And the idea that he would choose to end NATURAL is just speculation.
It is partly his manga, after all.
Nothing can come from discussing this here!
I am going to ask him directly.
So it is true that you asked for the right to end a manga you hate?
They would never give him the right do something like that.
I have to get first place ten weeks in a row.
So I only need to come in first place for five more weeks!
I will definitely get 1st in the next five weeks and end a manga.
He came in first with a large lead in this week's initial ranking.
That means he actually has only four more weeks to go.
Tell us what manga you want to end!
The one I want to end...
Was not it supposed to be a manga you hate?
I hate not being able to end something in the way that I want.
I know that the editing department does not want to end a popular manga.
The magazine is trying to make a profit, and I understand that.
But before I started drawing, I made a resolution.
I resolved to end my manga when I want to: at the height of its popularity, in the coolest way possible.
It looks like I will be able to do that, and I could not be happier.
The Chief wanted me to continue the manga if possible, but he came around soon enough.
And that is when he said you had to come in 1st for ten weeks straight.
After I come in 1st for ten weeks in a row, I then have ten weeks to wrap the story up and end it.
That is the condition I gave.
What happens if you do not come in 1st for ten weeks in a row?
Then I cannot end the series.
It would not be cool if another manga got first place.
Should that happen, I would try again to come in 1st for ten consecutive weeks.
Then, I would end my manga.
If I cannot do that, I have to keep drawing the series until it gets canceled.
Getting canceled or staying in first place...
If this do not concern NATURAL, I am leaving.
Should you continue drawing a popular manga just because it is popular,
or should you end it when you want to?
I can understand wanting to end it in the best way that you can.
But it will hurt Shounen Jack if CROW ends.
If it was me, I would not end my manga while it is still popular.
It would be such a waste!
I think you should continue while it is still popular.
Niizuma already has all the money he could ever need!
He should end his manga now and just enjoy himself!
Work is just meant to earn you enough money to live on, anyway!
Hiramaru, that is not what we are talking about here.
Well, even if you end CROW, you have still got NATURAL.
I would like to do another manga of my own one day.
I am not against you ending CROW the way you want.
But I do not want you to end it this way, either.
You are the artist we have always looked up to.
and excuse me for saying this, but I do not want you to end it now.
We have always wanted to surpass him.
I do not want things to end without us ever having succeeded!
If he ended it now, it would be like he quit while he was ahead.
if we do not want him to end it, we need to overtake him!
So sorry, but CROW are not ending!
Because I am going to pass you!
I understand how Fukuda and Ashirogi feel.
Even if I am not against Niizuma ending it as he wants to,
as his rival, I want to surpass him.
We all can agree on that.
Yeah, I want to surpass CROW, too.
I want to pass him and prevent him from ending it.
It would be awesome if I were able to do it.
CROW is at the height of its climax!
I did not throw out manuscript after manuscript only to lose to the likes of you guys!
Now you have said it, Master Niizuma.
Coming here has gotten us fired up.
I will not let you end your manga in such a cool way!
If anyone manages to beat me even once before I finish my final manuscript,
He will not end it if we beat him!
I want to get first place with Hiramaru.
I will win and achieve my dream!
Climax of the Sky Prison saga!!
Climax of the Sky Prison saga!!
I do not know what your goal is, but please spare me!
As soon as I reach my goals, it all falls through again
We met after such a long time
Has the mood changed for us?
It seemed like more fun back then
Do not stop screaming, do not stop struggling
You have done enough for others
I still, still have something I have not told you yet
Beyond each of my dreams lies yet another dream
Whenever I am close to fulfilling my goals, all effort becomes fruitless
We walk ahead, hold each other, and with little things
we support each other to reach what we promised
When we lack confidence, we put a hand to our heart
and reread the pages we assembled into a story
They lead up to today and continue into the morrow
until the day that our dreams come true
